div.p:
Before I came hither I had ſeen the Epitaph of that Proculus who lies interr'd in St. Proculus's Church in this City;


Si procul à Proculo, Proculi campana fuiſſet;

Jam procul à Proculo, Proculus ipſe foret.



But I always fancy'd, according to the common Opinion, that St. Proculus's Bell had knock'd out his Nameſake's Brains; whereas I'm inform'd here, that this Proculus being a very ſtudious perſon, accuſtom'd himſelf for ſeveral years to riſe every Morning at the ſound of that Bell; which was at laſt the occaſion of his death.

